I've added a number of infix operators, fixed a few issues, added unification to `Expr` class. Pylance has a bug that does not allow assigning a generic function to a generic parameter in a class and being able to call that function normally, as I wanted to use with my @Infix decorator. Wrote the proof that 0 is unique using the infix proof style and I kinda like it.
